Package: xtop
Version: 0.41.0-1
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libc6
Recommends: postgresql, journalctl, docker-compose
Installed-Size: 23350
Maintainer: Farhan Tahir <farhan.003@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/ftahirops/xtop
Description: Incident-first root-cause analysis console for Linux
 xtop is a terminal-based system monitor with ranked root-cause hypotheses,
 evidence scoring, and eBPF deep diagnostics. v0.41.0 adds a built-in
 end-to-end wizard: `sudo xtop setup` provisions a full fleet hub (Postgres
 role+db, auth token, systemd unit, /health probe, dashboard URL) or joins
 this host as an agent in under 30 seconds. Includes `xtop hub init`,
 `xtop hub token`, `xtop hub reset-token`, `xtop hub status`, `xtop agent
 init`, `xtop agent status` as non-interactive forms for scripts.
